-- Santander says to meet half of 2014-2016 cost savings target this year
-- 
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 05:20AM EDT
-- None



SANTANDER, Spain, March 28 (Reuters) - Spain's biggest bank Santander <SAN.MC> chief executive officer Javier Marin on Friday said the lender would make this year half of the 1.5 billion euros ($2 billion) cost savings it plans to achieve by 2016.

